{"type":"message","id":"bb2559c7","parentId":"25c17cc4","timestamp":"2026-04-02T17:53:31.262Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand my owned files. Let me summarize:\n\n**Owned files:**\n1. `rack_node_shell.lua` - The generic rack node shell component (function that returns a shell table)\n2. `rack_node_shell.ui.lua` - Static UI definition for rack node shell (declarative table)\n3. `rack_container.lua` - Uses `RackNodeShell` component, has 9 invocations\n4. `midisynth_view.ui.lua` - Does NOT import rack_node_shell directly, but has comments referencing \"rack-node\"\n\n**Task:**\n- Rename `rack_node_shell.lua` → `rack_module_shell.lua`\n- Rename `rack_node_shell.ui.lua` → `rack_module_shell.ui.lua`\n- Rename `RackNodeShell` → `RackModuleShell` (in rack_container.lua)\n- Update require from `components.rack_node_shell` to `components.rack_module_shell`\n\n**Hard constraints:**\n- Same repo, owned files only\n- Do NOT edit midisynth.lua or rack specs files\n- Do NOT restructure UI logic\n- NEVER run builds\n- NO cmake, ninja, standalone, VST\n- Verification only via `luac -p`, `rg`, safe python\n\n**First steps:**\n1. Check current directory structure\n2. Rename files with mv\n3. Update require statements in rack_container.lua\n4. Update variable name RackNodeShell → RackModuleShell in rack_container.lua\n5. luac -p all owned files\n6. rg for any remaining old names in owned files\n\nThe midisynth_view.ui.lua doesn't import rack_node_shell, but has comments about \"rack-node\". The brief says \"owned files only\" so I should update comments in midisynth_view.ui.lua if they reference the old terminology.\n\nLet me summarize this for the user.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\n### Owned Files (4)\n| File | Purpose | Imports rack_node_shell? |\n|------|---------|--------------------------|\n| `rack_node_shell.lua` | Generic shell component (function-based) | N/A (defines it) |\n| `rack_node_shell.ui.lua` | Static UI shell definition (declarative) | N/A (defines it) |\n| `rack_container.lua` | Rack layout host with 9 `RackNodeShell()` invocations | **Yes** - `local RackNodeShell = require(\"components.rack_node_shell\")` |\n| `midisynth_view.ui.lua` | Main view layout (palette cards, keyboard, etc.) | No - only has \"rack-node\" in comments |\n\n### Canonical Renames Required\n```\nrack_node_shell.lua        → rack_module_shell.lua\nrack_node_shell.ui.lua     → rack_module_shell.ui.lua\nRackNodeShell              → RackModuleShell\ncomponents.rack_node_shell → components.rack_module_shell\n```\n\n### Hard Constraints Acknowledged\n- **Same repo, owned files only** - Will not touch midisynth.lua or rack specs\n- **No build commands** - No cmake, ninja, standalone, VST\n- **No restructuring** - Pure rename only, logic untouched\n- **Safe verification only** - `luac -p`, `rg`, python\n\n### First Steps (awaiting GO)\n1. `mv` rename the two shell files\n2. Update `rack_container.lua`: change require path + variable name + all 9 invocations\n3. Update comment references in `midisynth_view.ui.lua` (\"rack-node\" → \"rack-module\")\n4. `luac -p` all 4 owned files\n5. `rg` verify no old names remain in owned files\n\n**No unresolved imports in my owned files** - the only cross-file dependency is `rack_container.lua` requiring the shell, which I'm renaming. Other workers handle spec files and midisynth.lua.\n\nSend **GO** when ready."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding-plan","model":"kimi-for-coding","usage":{"input":10045,"output":794,"cacheRead":4608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15447,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775152392536,"responseId":"msg_n20UJdBuHOxICmKn9HAS2Qm7"}}
